What are the coordinates of point $F$? Each small square is $0.5$ of a unit.
[tikz]
\begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.6]
\draw[step=0.5,gray!18] (-4,-4) grid (4,4);
\draw[step=1,gray!40] (-4,-4) grid (4,4);
\draw[<->,thick] (-4.4,0)--(4.4,0) node[right] {$x$};
\draw[<->,thick] (0,-4.4)--(0,4.4) node[above] {$y$};
\foreach \x in {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4} \node[below,font=\scriptsize] at (\x,0) {$\x$};
\foreach \y in {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4} \node[left,font=\scriptsize] at (0,\y) {$\y$};
\fill (-2.5,-1.5) circle (2.2pt);
\node[below left,font=\footnotesize] at (-2.5,-1.5) {$F$};
\end{tikzpicture}
[/tikz]

What are the coordinates of point $K$ on the $x$-axis? Each small square is $0.5$ of a unit.
[tikz]
\begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.6]
\draw[step=0.5,gray!18] (-4,-4) grid (4,4);
\draw[step=1,gray!40] (-4,-4) grid (4,4);
\draw[<->,thick] (-4.4,0)--(4.4,0) node[right] {$x$};
\draw[<->,thick] (0,-4.4)--(0,4.4) node[above] {$y$};
\foreach \x in {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4} \node[below,font=\scriptsize] at (\x,0) {$\x$};
\foreach \y in {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4} \node[left,font=\scriptsize] at (0,\y) {$\y$};
\fill (2.5,0) circle (2.2pt);
\node[above,font=\footnotesize] at (2.5,0.15) {$K$};
\end{tikzpicture}
[/tikz]

What do points $P$ and $Q$ have in common about their positions?
[tikz]
\begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.6]
\draw[step=0.5,gray!18] (-4,-4) grid (4,4);
\draw[step=1,gray!40] (-4,-4) grid (4,4);
\draw[<->,thick] (-4.4,0)--(4.4,0) node[right] {$x$};
\draw[<->,thick] (0,-4.4)--(0,4.4) node[above] {$y$};
\foreach \x in {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4} \node[below,font=\scriptsize] at (\x,0) {$\x$};
\foreach \y in {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4} \node[left,font=\scriptsize] at (0,\y) {$\y$};
\fill (-3,1) circle (2.2pt);
\node[above left,font=\footnotesize] at (-3,1) {$P$};
\fill (-3,-2) circle (2.2pt);
\node[below left,font=\footnotesize] at (-3,-2) {$Q$};
\end{tikzpicture}
[/tikz]

$P$, $Q$ and $R$ are three vertices of a rectangle with sides parallel to the axes. What are the coordinates of the fourth vertex $S$? Each small square is $0.5$ of a unit.
[tikz]
\begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.6]
\draw[step=0.5,gray!18] (-4,-4) grid (4,4);
\draw[step=1,gray!40] (-4,-4) grid (4,4);
\draw[<->,thick] (-4.4,0)--(4.4,0) node[right] {$x$};
\draw[<->,thick] (0,-4.4)--(0,4.4) node[above] {$y$};
\foreach \x in {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4} \node[below,font=\scriptsize] at (\x,0) {$\x$};
\foreach \y in {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4} \node[left,font=\scriptsize] at (0,\y) {$\y$};
\draw[thick] (-2,2)--(1.5,2)--(1.5,-1);
\fill (-2,2) circle (2.2pt);
\node[above left,font=\footnotesize] at (-2,2) {$P$};
\fill (1.5,2) circle (2.2pt);
\node[above right,font=\footnotesize] at (1.5,2) {$Q$};
\fill (1.5,-1) circle (2.2pt);
\node[below right,font=\footnotesize] at (1.5,-1) {$R$};
\end{tikzpicture}
[/tikz]
